{"cwd": "/tmp/cch-sandboxes/20260619T144033/websearch-tool", "duration_ms": 6776, "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "session_id": "<SESSION_ID>", "tool_input": {"query": "claude code hooks"}, "tool_name": "WebSearch", "tool_response": {"durationSeconds": 6.7761583700000045, "query": "claude code hooks", "results": [{"content": [{"title": "Claude Code Hooks (2026): Block Claude Reading .env + 30 Hook Events, JSON Input, Exit Codes", "url": "https://www.morphllm.com/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: The Feature You’re Ignoring While Babysitting Your AI | by Lakshmi Narasimhan | Medium", "url": "https://medium.com/@lakshminp/claude-code-hooks-the-feature-youre-ignoring-while-babysitting-your-ai-789d39b46f6c"}, {"title": "GitHub - karanb192/claude-code-hooks: 🪝 A growing collection of useful Claude Code hooks. Copy, paste, customize.", "url": "https://github.com/karanb192/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "GitHub - disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery: Master Claude Code Hooks · GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery"}, {"title": "Claude Code hooks explained: the missing layer between prompts and production", "url": "https://joseparreogarcia.substack.com/p/claude-code-hooks-explained-the-missing"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Automate Your AI Coding Workflow", "url": "https://www.ksred.com/claude-code-hooks-a-complete-guide-to-automating-your-ai-coding-workflow/"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks Complete Guide — Automate and Enforce Rules Reliably - SmartScope", "url": "https://smartscope.blog/en/generative-ai/claude/claude-code-hooks-guide/"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Complete Guide to All 12 Lifecycle Events", "url": "https://claudefa.st/blog/tools/hooks/hooks-guide"}, {"title": "Claude Code hooks 是用户定义的 shell 命令,在 Claude Code 生命周期的各个点执行。Hooks 提供对 Claude Code 行为的确定性控制,确保某些操作总是发生,而不是依赖 LLM 选择运行它们。", "url": "https://docs.anthropic.com/zh-CN/docs/claude-code/hooks-guide"}], "tool_use_id": "srvtoolu_01Mx94gZw1FbeyduxT4wX7w2"}, "Based on the search results, here's what Claude Code hooks are:\n\n## Overview\n\nClaude Code hooks fire user code at fixed points in the agent lifecycle. In Claude Code a hook is a shell command that reads JSON from stdin and signals back through exit codes and stdout JSON.\n\n## Key Concept\n\nThink of hooks like git hooks, but for your AI agent. You define handlers - shell commands, LLM prompts, or even sub-agents - that fire automatically at specific points during Claude Code's execution, such as before a tool runs, after a file gets edited, when the agent decides to stop, or when a session starts.\n\n## Main Advantage\n\nThe critical difference from prompt-based rules is that hooks are guaranteed to execute. If you set up a PreToolUse hook that blocks writes to .env files, it will always block them.\n\n## Common Use Cases\n\nHooks let you intercept events and run shell commands automatically. For example: run your formatter when Claude edits a file, send yourself a Slack message when Claude finishes a task, or run your linter before Claude tries to commit.\n\n## Lifecycle Events\n\nKey hook types include PreToolUse and PostToolUse, as well as UserPromptSubmit, Stop, and SubagentStop, among others available in Claude Code."], "searchCount": 1}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_019XSTLh6iVaUKqPJdWLjJnk", "transcript_path": "<TRANSCRIPT_PATH>"}
